s.  At the end of the day the actions are completed, re-entered or voided are checked off.\r\n', 'CLM Products', '', '', '[]'), ('774', 'Acquisition ', 'Acquisition instructional routines are \\\'Stimulus Control\\\' operations. They include a manipulation of the antecedents and the consequences. Acquisition routines are used to teach NEW knowledge forms (e.g., concepts, verbal associations, rules, and cognitive strategies).  How well the formats are designed to teach knowledge forms directly eases the task of developing a NEW response. Correct learner responses are reinforced on a continuous schedule of reinforcement.\r\nAcquisition routines are used to establish new repertoires or new responses. For example, when the learner can give the same response to an untaught example of a NEW concept, there is some evidence that a learner is acquiring the concept.  That is, when a learner says, \\\"dog\\\" when he sees on untaught example of a dog, we can say that he is beginning to learn the NEW concept, \\\"dog.\\\"   Note: detailed guidelines for teaching noun concepts and verbal associations are taught in Unit 9B.\r\nEnglemann and Carnine (1982, 1990) suggest that the initial teaching concepts should be practiced using a generalization routine, as soon as possible.    Refer to the CLM Curriculum for the precise acquisition routines per repertoire in the form of formats.\r\n', 'Instructional Routines', '', '', '{\"0\":{\"1004013\":\"0.04a3\"},\"9b\":{\"1901022\":\"9.01b2\",\"1901042\":\"9.01d2\",\"1901051\":\"9.01e1\",\"190105201\":\"9.01e2a\",\"1901055\":\"9.01e5\",\"1901059\":\"9.01e9\",\"1901061\":\"9.01f1\",\"1901074\":\"9.01g4\",\"1901091\":\"9.01i1\",\"1901094\":\"9.01i4\",\"1901101\":\"9.01j1\",\"1901103\":\"9.01j3\",\"1901105\":\"9.01j5\",\"1903021\":\"9.03b1\",\"1903022\":\"9.03b2\",\"1903023\":\"9.03b3\",\"1903024\":\"9.03b4\",\"1903033\":\"9.03c3\",\"190401\":\"9.04a\",\"190402\":\"9.04b\"},\"9A1-3\":{\"190001190\":\"9A.04e5\",\"190001170\":\"9A.04e3\",\"190001180\":\"9A.04e4\",\"190000210\":\"9A.01c5\",\"190000020\":\"9A.01a2\"},\"\":{\"60409193\":\"DI_1.93\",\"32100802\":\"210.08b\"}}'), ('771', '4.601 Listener (adhere to)', 'Learner performs the \\\'best\\\' actions for the day-to-day context when given an applicable rule and the \\\'if-then directions.\\\'\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('772', '4.701 Observer (imitate)', 'Learner performs the modeled 3-4 part sequence of actions.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('773', '4.801 Problem Solver (operate)', 'Learner attempts to solve the problem by manipulating the parts of the objects, seeks solution to problem for at least a couple of minutes, does not have to solve the problem.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('769', '4.504 Participator (peer-directed)', 'Learner works and plays cooperatively with peers (e.g., follows the rules, performs peer\\\'s directions, uses manners-says \\\'please\\\' and \\\'thank you,\\\' asks peers for assistance, provides peers assistance).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('770', '4.505 Participator (n-d: Transitions)', 'Learner uses time productively to complete assignments, change activities, and participate in activities without interrupting others.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('768', '4.503 Participator (semi-directed)', 'Learner works continuously to complete the three assigned tasks (i.e., skips \\\'difficult\\\' parts of the task(s) but complete parts that are firm), waits up to 15 minutes before asking for assistance, and uses time productively while waiting for assistance (e.g., does homework assignments or other activities as directed by T).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('761', '4.305 Reader (textual)', 'Learner reads the story twice. On the first reading the L sounds out each word and then says the word. On the second reading the L reads the fast way.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('762', '4.306 Reader (textual)', 'Learner reads each word the fast way.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('763', '4.307 Reader (intraverbal)', 'After rereading a sentence, the L answers the Tteachers who, what, where, when, and why questions.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('764', '4.401 Writer (copy text)', 'Learner copies the sentence, within the lines, on the worksheet.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('765', '4.402 Writer (taking dictation)', 'Learner writes the word problem, (e.g., 5+3=[  ]) or the word dictated (e.g., was) on line.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('766', '4.501 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner performs 3 consecutive sets of 20 responses; each set contains a mix of 10 firm, 8 not firm &amp; 2 NEW\r\nNote:  Waiting quietly when it is not L\\\'s turn to respond is counted as a correct response\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('767', '4.502 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner responds on signal in unison for 3 consecutive sets of 20 responses (Each set contains 10 FIRM, 8 NOT firm, &amp; 2 NEW items).\r\nNote:  Waiting quietly when it it not L\\\'s turn to respond is counted as a correct response.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('759', '4.302 Reader (textual)', 'Learner reads the known sounds as fast as s/he can given 12 rows of 10 letters per row; T sets timer for 60 seconds.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('760', '4.304 Reader (intraverbal)', 'Learner sounds out the word and then says it fast\r\nwhen T says, \\\"What word?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('758', '4.301 Reader (echoic)', 'Learner repeats the sentence, from memory, at a normal speaking rate\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('755', '4.108 Observer (tact)', 'Learner studies the pictures or objects for a few seconds and answers the T\\\'s question, (e.g., \\\"Why are the men the same/different?\\\").\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('756', '4.201 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner asks for \\\"advice\\\" to solve a problem with another person; describes problem with enough detail for T to provide a course of action (e.g., \\\"I need help, John is hitting me with his pencil during silent reading\\\".)\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('757', '4.202 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner spontaneously asks peers for potential reinforcers (e.g., for help, to not harm him, to play ____ with him and/or to take turns with NEW item).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('750', '4.009 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner states the rule (e.g., \\\"If you can eat it, it\\\'s food\\\" ) when asked \\\"What\\\'s the rule about food?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('751', '4.01 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers the question with a complete statement and uses the correct tense (e.g.,\\\"The man opened the trunk before he fixed the tire\\\").\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('752', '4.103 Observer (tact)', 'Learner describes the action(s) of a particular person when T asks a detailed question;   (e.g.,\\\"Talking with Jake\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('753', '4.106 Observer (tact)', 'Learner names the location (e.g., \\\"The Dentist\\\'s Office\\\"), some of the things (e.g.,\\\"a drill\\\"), and some of the people (e.g., \\\"a patient\\\") in the location when T shows picture.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('754', '4.107 Observer (tact)', 'Learner  looks at and scans the objects and/or persons for a few seconds and then tells T how they are the same and different. (e.g. \\\"They are the same because they can fly\\\" and \\\"They are different because a bird is an animal and a plane is a vehicle\\\").\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('749', '4.008 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers the questions with the information, (e.g., \\\"A person who watches people swim\\\" or \\\"A lifeguard\\\"), when T asks common information questions.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('748', '4.007 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers each question with the appropriate descriptive words. (e.g., T asks, \\\"Why does a doctor need a thermometer\\\") and L answers by saying, (\\\"A doctor needs a thermometer to find out if you\\\'re sick.\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('747', '4.006 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers \\\"if-then\\\" and \\\"wh-questions\\\" with a complete statement, For example, \\\"If someone teases me, I walk away.\\\"\r\n[accept any reasonable answer]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('746', '4.003 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers the first question with a \\\"yes\\\" or \\\"no\\\" and answers second question with \\\"Because a (e.g., dog) is (e.g., not a tool)\\\" when T says, \\\"Why did you say yes/no?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('740', '3.504 Participator (peer-directed)', 'Learner participates in peer-directed conditions with minimal assistance from the T who is 3-5 ft. away. For example, invites peer to play a game, takes turns, follows the directions given by the peer, and directs peer.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('741', '3.505 Participator (n-d: Transitions)', 'Learner selects activities, participates in the activities, and changes activities promptly without emitting annoying and/or injurious behaviors.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('742', '3.601 Listener (adhere to)', 'Learner performs the sequence of 2-3 detailed actions as directed, with T\\\'s product displayed as an example of what\\\'s expected.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('743', '3.701 Observer (imitate)', 'Learner performs the modeled two-step sequence of actions.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('745', '4.001 Talker (echoic)', 'Learner repeats modeled if-then sentence or rule (e.g., \\\"First wash your hands then get one cookieIf Mary washes her hands she can eat a cookie\\\").\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('744', '3.801 Problem Solver (operate)', 'Learner solves problem by looking for the essential items, that is, he scans general area in order to find the items (e.g., opens the door, scans the shelves and floor for the things, finds first one &amp; continues to look for next thing).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('739', '3.503 Participator (semi-directed)', 'Learner works continuously to complete the three assigned tasks (i.e., skips \\\'difficult\\\' parts of the task(s) but completes parts that are firm), does not ask the T for assistance during the first 5 minutes, and waits for help for up to 5 minutes after asking for assistance without annoying behaviors.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('733', '3.305 Reader (textual)', 'Learner touches each word as instructed, sounds out each word and says it fast.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('734', '3.307 Reader (intraverbal)', 'After rereading a sentence, the L answers the teachers who, what, and where questions.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('735', '3.401 Writer (copy text)', 'Learner copies a very simple sentence (story).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('736', '3.402 Writer (taking dictation)', 'Learner writes the letter as dictated, e.g., L writes \\\"m\\\" when T says \\\"mmm\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('737', '3.501 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner performs 3 consecutive sets of 20 responses (each set contains 15 firm &amp; 5 NEW items); responds when items are FIRM but does NOT respond or guess on the content that has NOT been learned. 1:10 context.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('738', '3.502 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner responds on signal in unison for 3 consecutive sets of 20 responses (Each set contains 15 firm &amp; 5 NEW items); responds when items are FIRM  but does NOT respond or guess on the content that has NOT been learned. 1:10 context.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('732', '3.304 Reader (intraverbal)', 'Learner sounds out the word and then says it fast when T says \\\"Sound it out\\\" (pause) \\\"Say it fast.\\\"\r\n[Use FIRM words only]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('729', '3.201 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner asks T to help solve the problem with a NEW task; describes the problem with amount of detail required for T to provide a course of action (e.g., \\\"I need help cutting the shapes\\\").\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('730', '3.301 Reader (echoic)', 'Learner L repeats and sustains the letter sounds;  sustains letter sounds between the sounds in words; For example, \\\'rrruuunnn\\\' with no pausing between sounds.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('731', '3.302 Reader (textual)', 'Learner reads the known sounds as fast as s/he can given 8 rows of 10 letters per row; T sets timer for 60 seconds.\r\n[Learner touches letter and reads each quickly]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('728', '3.107 Observer (tact)', 'Learner tells T how the displayed people or objects are the same; e.g., \\\"The boys are running\\\" or \\\"They are running\\\"; shown 2-3 pictures.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('722', '3.009 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner states two things known about the category, (e.g.,\\\"A plant needs dirt\\\" and \\\"Plants have leaves\\\") .\r\n[accept any reasonable answers]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('723', '3.101 Observer (tact)', 'Learner answers questions with a \\\"yes or no\\\" response for given description (attributes, location of object, and opposites) of  an item.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('724', '3.102 Observer (tact)', 'Learner says the name of the PART(s) of the object (e.g., says \\\'legs\\\' when T touches that part of a table).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('725', '3.103 Observer (tact)', 'Learner labels action and includes the proper possessive pronoun; e.g., \\\"Holding his hands over his head.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('726', '3.104 Observer (tact)', 'Learner answers detailed \\\"where\\\" questions (e.g., \\\"where is the wet paper towel?\\\") about the location of objects and people; (e.g., \\\"under the chair\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('727', '3.105 Observer (tact)', 'Learner labels an attribute (i.e., size or shape of objects or features of people) of objects or people when T touches the item; e.g., L says, \\\"Full\\\" after T touches a full glass of water.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('721', '3.008 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers question with the information, (e.g., \\\"A dentist is a person who fixes teeth\\\")  when a T asks a question about common information.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('720', '3.007 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner provides the appropriate type of answer to the given \\\"type of question\\\" (e.g., when T asks a \\\"where\\\" question, then the L replies with a \\\"where\\\" answer).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('718', '3.005 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner makes a complete statement about the action that includes the proper pronouns: \\\"We are touching our shoulders.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('719', '3.006 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers \\\"wh-questions\\\" with a complete statement. For example \\\"My sister\\\'s first name is Mary.\\\"\r\n[accept any reasonable answers]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('717', '3.004 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner labels object using descriptors and when directed makes a complete statement about a category of objects/people. For example, \\\"This vehicle is a yellow car?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('716', '3.001 Talker (echoic)', 'Learner repeats a modeled descriptive sentence (e.g., \\\"Mary is eating a cookie\\\") without item displayed.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('715', 'CAPTURE, ARRANGE, and WITHHOLD', 'Three key ways to use reinforcement\r\n', 'FLUENCY CARDS', '', 'Unit 2', '{\"2\":{\"1210011\":\"2.10a1\"},\"9A1-3\":{\"190000520\":\"9A.03f3\"},\"\":{\"118370\":\"2pt.10a1\"}}'), ('711', '2.601 Listener (adhere to)', 'Learner performs 7-10 two-step actions, each with detailed components, as directed across a variety of situations (e.g., transitioning and work contexts).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('708', '2.504 Participator (peer-directed)', 'Learner participates in a preferred activity (e.g., table game) with T\\\'s assistance (e.g., invites peer to play, takes turns, follows the directions given by the peer, and directs peer when assisted by the T.)\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('709', '2.505 Participator (n-d: Transitions)', 'Learner promptly puts things away in designated place, walks to assigned area without emitting annoying and/or injurious behaviors and promptly begins an assigned task.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('710', '2.506 Participator (n-d: Persists at Task)', 'Learner persists at getting the not firm part to come out right (i.e., tries at least a couple of ways to get the task to come out right, then asks for help and makes the necessary corrections); L may say \\\"I did it!!!\\\" when s/he completes the assigned task.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('714', '2.801 Problem Solver (operate)', 'Learner solves problem by looking for the essential thing in location described by T,  that is, he moves large and small objects in order to find it  (i.e., moves the chair, opens a container, and pushes the objects around to find the essential thing)\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('713', '2.702 Observer (match to sample)', 'Learner matches the 4-6 part pattern to assemble the product; objects or pictures positioned as designated by T\\\'s sample.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('712', '2.701 Observer (imitate)', 'Learner performs the specific set of actions in the sequence performed by the T (e.g., follows the direction and imitates the action performed or imitates the action and follows the direction).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('706', '2.502 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner responds on signal for 3 consecutive sets of 20 responses, that is, responds in unison with the group of learners (2 sets contain 15 FIRM &amp; 5 NOT firm items).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('707', '2.503 Participator (semi-directed)', 'Learner completes assigned tasks (2 firm and 1 newly firmed) and seeks assistance as directed by the Teacher (e.g., raises hand or quietly walks to the Teacher and waits for assistance); L may say, \\\"I did it all by myself.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('705', '2.501 Participator (teacher-directed)', 'Learner performs 3 consecutive sets of twenty responses (2 sets contain  15 firm &amp; 5 not firm items); 1:4 context.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('699', '2.301 Reader (echoic)', 'Learner repeats and sustains the letter sound when T signals for a response by holding up an index finger: L responds on signal in a small group.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('700', '2.302 Reader (textual)', 'Learner reads the sounds as fast as s/he can given  4 rows of 10 letters per row.\r\n[Learner touches letter and reads each quickly]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('701', '2.304 Reader (intraverbal)', 'Learner says the word fast, (e.g., \\\"rope\\\"), when T sounds out a word and says \\\"Say it fast.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('702', '2.307 Reader (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers each simple question with the detail requested (e.g., \\\'baby bear\\\') or fills in the missing detail to an open ended sentence (e.g., in the chair) immediately after the story is read or restated.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('703', '2.401 Writer (copy text)', 'Learner copies her first name legibly.\r\n[response form consists of all letters copied on the same line, each word is written well enough so that at least two people can read the letters printed]\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('704', '2.402 Writer (taking dictation)', 'Learner writes the letter that corresponds to a sound on the designated line.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('698', '2.203 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner may calmly say, for example, \\\"I don\\\'t want it, thank you\\\" or \\\"I want a blue crayon,\\\" if s/he prefers another color crayon.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('697', '2.202 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner spontaneously asks \\\"Where is the/my ____?\\\", (item not visible).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('692', '2.102 Observer (tact)', 'Learner states what kind of item is displayed in the picture (e.g., \\\"a  car\\\") across a variety of categories when T asks, \\\"What kind of vehicle is this?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('693', '2.103 Observer (tact)', 'Learner performs the action, labels the action, and uses the proper possessive pronoun, \\\"Touching my shoulder\\\"  in a small group of learners.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('694', '2.104 Observer (tact)', 'Learner says the location of the object (e.g., \\\"On the table\\\") when T says, \\\"Where is the___?\\\".\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('695', '2.105 Observer (tact)', 'Learner labels an attribute (e.g., size or color) of objects or people. For exmple, the learner says \\\"green\\\" when shown an apple and asked, \\\"What color is the apple?\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('696', '2.201 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner asks for specific object needed by saying, \\\"May I have a red crayon\\\" or asks for specific teacher action needed by saying, \\\"Open the jar, please\\\" when T sabotages the situation.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('691', '2.101 Observer (tact)', 'Learner answers questions with a \\\"yes or no\\\" response for given description (attributes and location of object) of an item.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('690', '2.006 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers questions posed by T. For example, when asked what his name is, he answers  \\\"Johnny Apple!\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('685', '2.001 Talker (echoic)', 'Learner repeats modeled detailed sentence (e.g., \\\"I wants two cookies\\\") without item displayed.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('686', '2.002 Talker (echoic)', 'Learner repeats modeled detailed phrase or statement (i.e., verb-ing plus noun; Name plus verb-ing plus noun; Mand plus attribute plus noun): \\\"That\\\'s my brother.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('687', '2.003 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner may answer one vehicle at a time \\\"a car \\\" (pause) \\\"a boat\\\" or learner may say \\\"a car and a boat\\\" when T randomly selects category from a minimum of four categories and says \\\"Name two______.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('688', '2.004 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner labels object using descriptors and when directed makes a complete statement about the item. For example, \\\"This is my car.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('689', '2.005 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner makes a complete statement that includes the proper pronoun/noun, the possessive pronoun, and the action performed: \\\"The boy is riding his bike.\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('679', '1.505 Participator (n-d: Transitions)', 'Learner selects variety of activities or objects, participates for about 15 consecutive minutes, and puts materials away in designated area (if there is one) within one minute without emitting annoying and/or injurious behaviors.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('680', '1.602 Listener (adhere to - touch)', 'Learner touches each picture of a category within 2 seconds when presented in a field of 1-12 pictures.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('681', '1.701 Observer (imitate)', 'Learner imitates, quickly and accurately, the specific action(s) modeled (e.g., holds up two fingers).\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('682', '1.702 Observer (match to sample)', 'Learner matches the four FIRM sets of similar cards on a 4X4 grid board (i.e., places the cards of each set in the designated row) and\r\nplaces 4-5 distractors aside; [response form consists of two rows matched].\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('683', '1.703 Observer (sorting)', 'Learner sorts 4 sets of  FIRM pictures to pictures by categories and places 3-4 distracters aside.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('684', '1.801 Problem Solver (operate)', 'Learner manipulates the parts of the object so they \\\"fit\\