ction s/he is performing with an item when asked, \\\"What are you doing?\\\"  (i.e., \\\"Holding your/my/a teddy.\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('669', '1.201 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner spontaneously travels and asks as expected for a \\\"missing\\\" part or teacher action by using phrase (e.g., \\\"My coat\\\"); waits up to 3 minutes.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('670', '1.202 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner spontaneously asks, \\\"What\\\'s that?\\\" when a NEW item is displayed by T.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('671', '1.203 Problem Solver (mand)', 'Learner calmly uses vocal behavior to turn down an offer of a NON-PREFERRED item, activity or T actions by using the phrase, \\\"No\\\" plus noun (e.g., \\\"No run!!!\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('662', '1.002 Talker (echoic)', 'Learner repeats a variety of modeled 2-word phrases, using firm words, as fast and as accurately as L can.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('663', '1.004 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner labels object (\\\"a car\\\") and when directed  makes a detailed statement about the item using his/her proper name, pronoun or whose item, or color of the item (\\\"Sara\\\'s[learner\\\'s name] car\\\" or \\\"My car\\\" or  \\\"Mommy car\\\" or \\\"Red car\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('665', '1.006 Talker (intraverbal)', 'Learner answers personal information question (e.g., \\\"How old are you?\\\")\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('666', '1.101 Observer (tact)', 'Learner answers questions with a \\\"yes\\\" or \\\"no\\\" quickly and accurately across 5 categories when T presents FIRM pictures.\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('664', '1.005 Talker (tact>intraverbal)', 'Learner labels the action and when directed makes a detailed personal statement or \\\"I\\\" statement about the action: \\\"Sara(learner\\\'s name) eating\\\" or \\\"I am eating\\\"\r\n', 'CLRA Facts', '', '', '[]'), ('658', '0.702 Observer (match to sample)', 'Learner comp